	<!-- Empire west 3 -->
	<Hero id="lord_1_11" spouse="Hero.lord_1_12" faction="Faction.clan_empire_west_3" text="{=vzR5CfuX}Crotor's family, the house of Dionicos, has taken charge of the empire's northwestern defenses for generations. The clan's leaders are more likely to keep the company of border raiders and scouts than senators in the capital. Crotor has backed Garios in the civil war, largely due to his innate sense of loyalty to a fellow comrade-in-arms."/>
	<Hero id="lord_1_111" father="Hero.lord_1_11" mother="Hero.lord_1_12" faction="Faction.clan_empire_west_3"/>
	<Hero id="lord_1_12" spouse="Hero.lord_1_11" faction="Faction.clan_empire_west_3" text="{=FbmWZdbg}Lysica is the wife of Crotor, a frontier lord in the western empire. Like many noblewomen in the border countries, she learned to ride, shoot, and lead men, often taking the lead in defending clan lands when her husband is away."/>
	<Hero id="lord_1_36" father="Hero.lord_1_11" mother="Hero.lord_1_12" faction="Faction.clan_empire_west_3" text="{=s2Wbx6bg}Phaea is a noblewoman of the house of Dionicos, traditional wardens of the empire's frontier with Battania. Like her mother, Lysica, she has trained to fight and to lead men in battle, so that the frontiers can still be defended when the clan patriarchs are away at war."/>
	<Hero id="lord_1_26" father="Hero.lord_1_11" mother="Hero.lord_1_12" faction="Faction.clan_empire_west_3"/>
